                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-07T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 7, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>113. I conveyed personally this morning to the Minister for Foreign Affairs and
                    Minister of War the contents of your telegram No. 42, September 6, 10 p.m. They
                    expressed the profound gratitude of their government for your prompt and
                    sympathetic action. In reply to the last paragraph they stated that during the
                    last 24 hours the situation has changed fundamentally in favor of the
                    Government, that all but three units of the Navy are now in their hands, and
                    that, although the large battleship is one of these units and is now moving
                    south, they are confident that the Government will be able to dominate soon the
                    situation with the means that it has at hand. Hence they believe it unnecessary
                    at this time to continue further with the request for war materials but will do
                    so if occasion arises.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
